        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 1:27PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 126 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 16
miles east of Yosemite South Entrance. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clover Meadow Wilderness Office and Green Mtn.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
